## Step 8 — Check for Outdated Statistics

Stale statistics cause SQL Server to choose inefficient execution plans — scanning entire tables instead of using indexes, burning unnecessary CPU:

```sql
-- Find tables with outdated statistics
SELECT 
    OBJECT_NAME(s.object_id)        AS table_name,
    s.name                          AS stats_name,
    sp.last_updated,
    sp.rows,
    sp.rows_sampled,
    sp.modification_counter,
    CAST(sp.modification_counter * 100.0 / 
         NULLIF(sp.rows, 0) AS DECIMAL(5,2))  AS modification_pct
FROM sys.stats s
CROSS APPLY sys.dm_db_stats_properties(s.object_id, s.stats_id) sp
WHERE sp.modification_counter > 0
ORDER BY sp.modification_counter DESC;
```

```sql
-- Update stats on a specific table
UPDATE STATISTICS [dbo].[YourTable] WITH FULLSCAN;

-- Update all stats across the entire database
EXEC sp_updatestats;
```

