## Root Cause Decision Tree

```
High CPU confirmed on SQL Server?
        │
        ├── CXPACKET high?
        │       └── YES → Parallelism problem
        │               ├── MAXDOP = 0? → Set MAXDOP to core count max 8 (Step 5)
        │               └── Cost Threshold = 5? → Increase to 50 (Step 5)
        │
        ├── Specific query using high avg_cpu_ms?
        │       └── YES → Query problem
        │               ├── High logical_reads? → Missing index (Step 6)
        │               ├── Fragmented indexes? → Rebuild indexes (Step 7)
        │               ├── Outdated stats? → Update statistics (Step 8)
        │               ├── max_cpu 10x avg_cpu? → Parameter sniffing (Step 9)
        │               └── CONVERT_IMPLICIT in plan? → Fix data types (Step 10)
        │
        ├── High recompile count?
        │       └── YES → Fix DDL or SET options in stored procs (Step 11)
        │
        ├── SOS_SCHEDULER_YIELD high + all schedulers busy?
        │       └── YES → CPU cores maxed out
        │               └── All queries tuned? → Resize VM to more vCPUs (Step 13.2)
        │
        └── Other process using CPU (not sqlservr.exe)?
                └── YES → Check antivirus, backup agents, monitoring tools
                        └── Exclude SQL data folders from antivirus scanning
```

